This paper deals with the issue of interference in wireless networks, specifically in Wi-Fi networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also proposes a joint power control and channel time scheduling algorithm, which involves optimization techniques, indicating that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of branch-and-bound global optimization technique, which is commonly used in multimedia applications, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of interference on network throughput and fairness, which could also place it in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category.
